<TITLE> Formalin testing to start in Karwan Bazaar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 13 (bdnews24.com)A formalin testing centre will begin operating in Karwan Bazaar Tuesday to ensure fish sold in the capital are free of the illegal preservative, an official said. "Traders have long used formalin to preserve fish, a chemical known to be hazardous to health," Monwar Hossain Akondo, deputy-secretary of the home ministry and coordinator of the project told bdnews24.com Monday. He said fisheries and livestock minister Abdul Latif Biswash would inaugurate the centre. "We decided to take this initiative after previous attempts to put an end to the use of formalin failed. Buyers can collect formalin kits from the centre to test their fish," said Akondo. Mohammad Imran Hossain, deputy secretary of the fisheries and livestock ministry, said more centres would soon be set up in other markets in the capital. bd
